SUMMARY:Passion for Fashion -1960's
DESCRIPTION:The Toronto Photography Group\n## Time & Location\n\nApr 30\, 
 2026\, 7:00 PM – 10:00 PM\nRevprint Studio 205 \, 146 Thirtieth St\, Eto
 bicoke\, ON M8W 3C4\, Canada\n\nyou can purchase tickets here or on our we
 bsite at www.wtpg.ngo\n\n## About the event\n\n### **Passion for Fashion 1
 960's edition Lighting Workshop**\n\n**Date:** Thursday\, May 30th 2026\n*
 *Time:** 7:00 PM – 10:00 PM\n**Instructor:** *Phil Sutherland* – Elinc
 hrom Ambassador & Executive Director\, West Toronto Photography Group\nMod
 el Anjali- gallery of images from previous workshop -This workshop feature
 s wardrobe selected by Adrianna Fulop and is a great selection of 1960's f
 ashion\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/1eaf19_b0ffafd7c26d4239b332
 5eeb9fdd1353~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_1686\,h_1000\,fp_0.50_0.50\,q_90/1eaf19_b0f
 fafd7c26d4239b3325eeb9fdd1353~mv2.webp)\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/
 media/1eaf19_92596e5378184ea5889dfcc24b7de610~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_1148\,h_68
 1\,fp_0.50_0.50\,q_90/1eaf19_92596e5378184ea5889dfcc24b7de610~mv2.webp)\n!
 [](https://static.wixstatic.com/media/1eaf19_002f118d046a4dfcb3756dc147865
 673~mv2.png/v1/fill/w_602\,h_500\,fp_0.50_0.50\,q_90/1eaf19_002f118d046a4d
 fcb3756dc147865673~mv2.webp)\n**Lighting Equipment:** Provided by **Elinch
 rom**\n**Location:** Revprint Studio 205 - 146 Thirtierth street unit 205\
 n**Workshop Size:** Limited to **6 participants**\n\n#### **Workshop Overv
 iew**\n\nJoin us for a fun and informative **Passion for Fashion photograp
 hy lighting and shooting workshop** designed to help you build skills and 
 portfolio images and technical skills in the art of Fashion lighting. Whet
 her you’re new to studio photography or looking to refine your lighting 
 technique\, this hands-on session will guide you through essential tools\,
  setups\, and creative lighting approaches.\nThis **three-hour\, small-gro
 up workshop** ensures plenty of individual attention\, shooting time\, and
  opportunities to ask questions.\n\n![](https://static.wixstatic.com/media
 /1eaf19_ab9a59de02574cfe89ec7b4e44fa0466~mv2.jpg/v1/fill/w_556\,h_554\,fp_
 0.50_0.50\,q_90/1eaf19_ab9a59de02574cfe89ec7b4e44fa0466~mv2.webp)\n![](htt
 ps://static.wixstatic.com/media/1eaf19_4ba5ca7767164053aa9e04013905f165~mv
 2.jpg/v1/fill/w_556\,h_554\,fp_0.50_0.50\,q_90/1eaf19_4ba5ca7767164053aa9e
 04013905f165~mv2.webp)\n\n#### **What You’ll Learn**\n\n1. **Studio Gear
 ** A detailed overview of lighting equipment\, modifiers\, and how we will
  use them for each lighting set up we build as a group ..\n2. **Studio Des
 ign & Setup**Understand how to plan and use studio space efficiently for p
 ortrait sessions.\n3. **Modifiers & Light Quality** Explore how different 
 modifiers affect your images as we utilize the Rotolaux modifiers from Eli
 nchrom in studio.\n4. **Building a Lighting Setup** As a group we will ste
 p-by-step construct professional portrait lighting setups using Elinchrom 
 lights and modifiers.\n5. **Hands-On Shooting Practice** Photograph our mo
 del Lilli in **multiple lighting setups that create strong and elegant lig
 hting** —each participant will have one-on-one shooting time and instruc
 tor feedback. You will get some stunning images for your portfolio from th
 e small group 3 hour portrait perfection lighting workshop\n\n#### **Who S
 hould Attend**\n\nThis workshop is ideal for photographers of all skill le
 vels who want to:\n\n* Learn or refresh the fundamentals of portrait and s
 tudio lighting or pick up a few new tricks\n* Get hands-on experience with
  professional lighting equipment from Elinchrom\n* Practice creating and r
 efining lighting setups that you can use to WOW clients\n* Build confidenc
 e shooting portraits in a studio environment while updating your portfolio
 \n\n#### **What to Bring**\n\n* A **DSLR or mirrorless camera** with a wor
 king hot-shoe\n* **Fresh batteries** and **formatted memory cards**\n* You
 r **favourite lens** (anything between 10mm–200mm works great)\n* Curios
 ity\, creativity\, and your passion for photography!\n\n#### **What’s In
 cluded**\n\n* Professional instruction and lighting gear provided by **Eli
 nchrom**\n* Access to a variety of light modifiers: reflectors\, umbrellas
 \, softboxes\, grids\, snoots\, and beauty dishes\n* A safe\, supportive\,
  and professional environment to learn and network\n* Dedicated time with 
 the model for individual shooting opportunities\n\n\\*\\*Time is money\, a
 nd we value yours.\\*\\*That’s why we keep our workshops efficient\, inf
 ormative\, and fun—so you leave inspired\, informed\, and ready to light
  your next portrait session like a pro.
